body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting our customer support. My name is Philip Ross and I represent Auto Dynamics, a trusted car dealership. May I please have your name?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi, my name is Nicole Coleman.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Nicole. Could you please provide me with your phone number so we can assist you better?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five one two three four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And may I also have your email address for follow-up purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email address is nicole.coleman@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Nicole. We will look into the issue regarding the product quality at our dealership.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I appreciate your help. I was feeling disappointed, but I hope it can be resolved.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Your feedback is valuable to us, Nicole. We will ensure to address your concerns promptly. Thank you for your time.
